  "title": "HSE & Facility Manager (Aerospace)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Location : Loyang, near pasir ris</strong><br /><strong>Industry : Aerospace</strong><br /><br />My client is seeking an experienced <strong>HSE & Facilities Manager</strong> to lead Health, Safety & Environment (HSE), facilities operations, and sustainability initiatives at our aerospace site. This is a key leadership role supporting safe operations, regulatory compliance, and continuous improvement in a dynamic manufacturing environment.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Lead and drive site-wide <strong>HSE strategy, governance, and compliance</strong> in line with regulatory and Group standards.</p></li><li><p>Implement, maintain, and continuously improve <strong>HSE Management Systems</strong> (ISO 14001, ISO 45001).</p></li><li><p>Identify and mitigate <strong>occupational, facility, and environmental risks</strong>; manage incident investigations and corrective actions.</p></li><li><p>Drive <strong>HSE performance indicators</strong>, reporting progress and insights to management.</p></li><li><p>Manage <strong>HSE teams/representatives</strong>, training programs, safety committees, and site-wide awareness initiatives.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate <strong>internal and external audits</strong>, certifications, and regulatory engagements.</p></li><li><p>Oversee <strong>facilities management</strong>, including building maintenance, vendors, contracts, and improvement projects.</p></li><li><p>Support <strong>energy efficiency and sustainability initiatives</strong> to reduce environmental impact.</p></li><li><p>Lead emergency preparedness, fire safety, and evacuation drills.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Engineering</strong> (Aviation / Aeronautical / Mechanical / Electrical / Electronic or related).</p></li><li><p><strong>Certified WSH Safety Officer</strong> (mandatory).</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>5 years’ HSE / EHS experience</strong>, preferably within the <strong>aerospace or manufacturing industry</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with <strong>ISO 14001 & ISO 45001</strong>; LEAN knowledge is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical, reporting, and problem-solving skills.</p></li><li><p>Proven leadership with the ability to engage stakeholders at all levels.</p></li><li><p>Highly organized, proactive, and able to manage emergencies and high-pressure situations.</p></li><li><p>Excellent communication skills and proficiency in <strong>Microsoft Office</strong>.</p></li></ul>",
